This paper focuses on creating a natural language interface for performing complex actions, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves interactive learning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The use of a community of users to teach a common system and build complex structures involves aspects of human-computer interaction (HCI), making cs.HC a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the development of a programming language, which falls under software engineering (SE) and machine learning (ML), making cs.SE and cs.LG possible sub-categories as well.
